AGI -&nbsp;The gup of Rome has postponed to trial three carabinieri in relation to the death of Stefano Cucchi, compared to what is reported in the process on the depistaggi. They are the Marshal Maurizio Bertolino, Captain Prospero Fortunato and Marshal Giuseppe Perri.
&nbsp;
The trial will begin on 25 September next to the monocratic judge of the eighth section. Compared to today's decision, which led to the referral to judgment of the three carabinieri, for a so-called 'Cucchi ter', it is remembered that Bertolino would lie to his superiors. In particular - according to the defendant -, in 2021 he would have said he did not know anything about the existence, in the station of the Carabinieri of Tor Sapienza, of a collector with acts related to the case Cucchi. It was confirmed by a colleague. Then, in the courtroom, having admitted to being aware of the dossier, he would falsely state that he had communicated everything to his superiors. Captain Prospero in service to the radius nucleus of Rome, would have written the false in the 'Memoriale di servizio' of 2 November 2018 indicating that a marshal and a deputy brigadiere, of his department, were engaged in other external services, while the one had been heard in the offices of the police and the other had accompanied him.
&nbsp;
According to the request for referral to judgment, in fact accepted by Judge Ciranna, Marshal Perri, of the radiomobile nucleus of Rome, then, heard as a witness in the courtroom, would have lied denying that he had asked the police to attend the interrogation in the police of the colleague he had accompanied. The crimes challenged by the three carabinieri are, in various ways, those of deceiving and ideological falsehood committed by the official public in public acts. In the proceedings, the Ministry of Defence is responsible for civil matters, while among the civilian parties there is also Riccardo Casamassima, one of the survivors who bravely managed to tell what he had seen, contributing in essence to ascertain the truth about the plague suffered by Cucchi in barracks. Civil Parties also the association Cittadinanzattiva, with lawyer Stefano Maccioni; the Party for the Protection of Military Rights; the three agents of the penitentiary who were accused in the first trial and then were acquitted.

